
[1]semitone

   SEM'ITONE, n. [semi and tone.] In music, half a tone; an interval of
   sound, as between mi and fa on the diatonic scale, which is only half
   the distance of an interval between ut and re, or sol and la. It is the
   smallest interval admitted in modern.
